**WHAT IS A DATA PACKET ? **
data packet is a small, formatted unit of data sent over a packet-switched network, such as the internet, when a large file is sent over network, system does not trasnmit all at once, instead the OS breaks the data down into millions of these bite sized packets so they can travel efficiently across network hardware withotu clogging the lines

**anatomy of a data packet : **
every data packet is divided into three disticnt structural parts, resembling a physical postal letter 
- **the header (envelope) : **header contaisn metadata required to route the packet to its destination, sits at the front of the packet and contains : **source IP Address, destinaton IP address, Packet number (**serial number of this specific packet in the stream), **protocol type (**what kind of packet is this, IPV4, OR IPV6

- **the payload (the letter inside) : **actual raw data being trasnmittedm tiny fragment of larger asset, such as a piece of an html page, snippet of VoIP phone call stream, few pizels of a JPEG image

**- The trailer : ** the trailer sits at the end of the packet and contaisn error checking mechanicsm, most notably a **cyclic reduncancy check (crc) or checksum**
          - when a packet arrives the receiving device calculates a mathematical value based on the bits inside the payload
          - if the calculates value matches the value stamped inside the trailer, the packet is healthy
